[SN]TITLE[SN]
Brad Jones: Bradford City sign ex-Liverpool goalkeeper

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
League One club Bradford City have signed Australia international and ex-Liverpool goalkeeper Brad Jones on a one-year contract.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Jones, 33, began his career at Middlesbrough and played 75 times for Boro before joining Liverpool in 2010.
He made 27 appearances in five seasons at Anfield, the last coming in a Premier League win at Burnley in December, and was released in June.
Jones will go into Bradford's squad for Tuesday's home game with Gillingham.
